

# About Jordan Young

## Global Director of Golf | Award-Winning Instructor | Golf Enthusiast

Jordan Young is a leading figure in the world of golf, blending decades of teaching excellence with high-level leadership in sports business. As **Director of Golf Operations at GameAbove Sports**, Jordan oversees a dynamic portfolio that includes managing eight professional golfers, providing technical advisory for career players, directing premium golf travel operations in the USA through Golf Traveller, leading the Eastern Michigan University (EMU) golf program, and driving global investments, sponsorships, and acquisitions in the golf space.

A passionate golf enthusiast at heart, Jordan remains deeply committed to growing the game through instruction. Whether working with touring professionals, competitive juniors, dedicated amateurs, or weekend players, he delivers personalized, results-driven coaching that helps golfers of all levels reach their full potential.

### Career Highlights
- **2013 National PGA Award for Player Development** – Recognized nationally for outstanding contributions to growing the game.
- **Michigan PGA Teacher of the Year** (2012) – Prestigious statewide honor for teaching excellence.
- **7-time Eastern Chapter PGA Teacher of the Year** – Consistent recognition for impact on students.
- **Golf Digest "Best in State" Ranking** and **Golf Tips Magazine Top 25 Instructor** – Peer and media acknowledgment of elite teaching status.
- **Featured Presenter** at the 2008 PGA Championship Learning Center, Oakland Hills Country Club.
- **Host of SPIN on GOLF** – Weekly radio show on WJR AM760, sharing insights and stories from the golf world.
- **CEO of ProScreenAi3D** – Leading innovation in golf simulation and training technology, including the AiSensor pressure mat.
- **Long-standing partnership with TaylorMade** – Major sponsor supporting custom fitting and player development.

### Coaching Philosophy
Jordan believes great golf begins with great fundamentals, clear communication, and a plan tailored to each individual. His approach combines modern technology (OnForm video analysis, pressure mat data, and launch monitor feedback) with on-course experience and a deep understanding of the mental side of the game.

From private one-on-one sessions and small-group programs to remote virtual coaching, Jordan makes world-class instruction accessible to everyone — whether you're chasing a tour card, breaking 80 for the first time, or simply wanting to enjoy the game more.

### Ready to Elevate Your Game?
Jordan welcomes golfers of all ages and abilities. Limited private instruction, group sessions, and remote coaching programs are available.

